TITLE: Forks in Fluent API C#
DESCRIPTION: Explains how to create forks in a fluent API by specifying multiple builder methods at the same step. The resulting API will offer all the specified methods at that step, but only one can be called.
SOURCE: https://github.com/m31coding/m31.fluentapi/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_23

LANGUAGE: cs
CODE:
```
[FluentMember(1, "OfAge")]
public int Age { get; private set; }

[FluentMethod(1)]
private void BornOn(DateOnly dateOfBirth)
{
    DateOnly today = DateOnly.FromDateTime(DateTime.Today);
    int age = today.Year - dateOfBirth.Year;
    if (dateOfBirth > today.AddYears(-age)) age--;
    Age = age;
}
```

LANGUAGE: cs
CODE:
```
...OfAge(22)...
...BornOn(new DateOnly(2002, 8, 3))...
```

